Mohammed Adamu, Nigeria's Inspector-General of Police, has ordered the Commissioner of Police in Ondo State, Bolaji Salami, to restore the security details of the state's deputy governor, Agboola Ajayi, with immediate effect. The directive was contained in a letter issued to the Ondo Police Commissioner through the Deputy Inspector General of Police, Department of Operations, Force headquarters Abuja. SaharaReporters exclusively obtained a copy of the letter on Monday morning with Ref. No CB: 2002/DOPS/FHQ/ABJ/VOL/77/168. The letter was signed on behalf of the IGP through Mr Austine Agbonlahor, Assistant Inspector-General of Police.Â 



